page.title: 02Colwick Woods
page.content: We arrived at Colwick woods at about 11 a.m. on the 5th May 1985. We stayed there for about 2 1/4 hours.The ground was hard. We did not see any mammals but we saw rabbit droppings by the golf course and mole hills on banks.We also saw a trail of hoove prints. Below a hazel tree there were some nut husks which suggest that squirrels had been around. I also counted the insects including slugs spiders and worms.I saw two ladybirds _ a two spot and a seven spot _ both of them on fern leaves.We also spotted two bees which flew past us, probably searching for nectar. We saw several gnats flying past us. Staying with flying insects, we saw a solitary wasp fly into the canopy. We also saw a cabbage white butterfly, flying from plant to plant also looking for food.
